\f1 Today is the anniversary of the death of Johannes Kepler, 
\f0 \uc0\u55356 \u56809 \u55356 \u56810 
\f1 German {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Johannes_Kepler"}}{\fldrslt astronomer}} who formulated three major laws of planetary motion which enabled {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://todayinsci.com/12/12_25.htm#NewtonIsaac"}}{\fldrslt Isaac Newton}} to devise the law of gravitation. Working from the carefully measured positions of the planets recorded by {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://todayinsci.com/12/12_14.htm#BraheTycho"}}{\fldrslt Tycho Brahe}}, Kepler mathematically deduced three relationships from the data: \
(1) the planets move in elliptical orbits with the Sun at one focus; \
(2) the radius vector sweeps out equal areas in equal times; \
(3) for two planets the squares of their periods are proportional to the cubes of their mean distances from the sun. \
Kepler suggested that the tides were caused by the attraction of the moon. He believed that the universe was governed by mathematical rules, but recognized the importance of experimental verification.\
\

\f0 \uc0\u55356 \u56814 \u55356 \u56825 
\f1 \'c8 oggi l\'92anniversario della morte di Johannes Kepler, italianizzato Keplero,
\f0  
\f2\fs28 \cf5 \cb6 \'e8 stato un {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomo"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 astronomo}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astrologia"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 astrologo}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matematico"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 matematico}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cosmologia_(astronomia)"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 cosmologo}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teoria_della_musica"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 teorico musicale}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Filosofia_naturale"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 filosofo della natura}} e {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teologo"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 teologo}} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germania"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 tedesco}}, che scopr\'ec empiricamente le {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leggi_di_Keplero"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 omonime leggi}} che regolano il movimento dei {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pianeti"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 pianeti}}.\cb1  \cb6 Professore di materie scientifiche in diverse universit\'e0 della {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germania"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 Germania}} e dell'{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Austria"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 Austria}} e protetto dell'{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imperatore_del_Sacro_Romano_Impero"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 Imperatore}} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rodolfo_II"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 Rodolfo II}}, Keplero, contemporaneo di {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galileo_Galilei"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 Galileo Galilei}}, fu un convinto sostenitore del {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sistema_copernicano"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 sistema copernicano}}.\
